        "excerpt": "Alert  You have a +5 bonus to Initiative, and you can’t be surprised.   Bonus Ribbons  You have an extra 2 ribbons of your choice. These ribbons can be from any category, even if you don’t have points in any power schools in that category.   Companion  You have a loyal companion, who might be a human follower, an animal you befriended, or a monster you tamed. Your companion has the stats of some creature of CR 1/4 or less (CR 1/2 if you’re level 5+, CR 1 if you’re level 9+, CR 2 if you’re level 13+, or CR 4 if you’re level 17+). You control your companion’s actions both in and out of combat. If your companion dies, you can spend a week of downtime to obtain a replacement.   Expertise  Choose two general skills you are proficient in. When you make a die roll with one of those skills, you add double your Prof instead of your normal Prof.   Skilled  Choose four general skills you are not proficient in. You gain proficiency in those skills.   Versatile Skill  Choose one combat skill or two general skills, then choose one attribute. Whenever you make a die roll with one of your chosen skills, you can choose to add your chosen attribute instead of the skill’s normal attribute.",
