        "title": "Invoker",
        "excerpt": "Powers          Name     Tier     Type     Description                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                      Divine Grace                  Novice                                                                                                             Glimpse of Redemption                  Novice                                                                                                             Lay on Hands                  Novice                                                                                                             Slayer's Oath                  Novice                                                                                     Litany against Wrath                  Veteran                                                                                                             Persistent Smite                  Veteran                                                                                                             Smite Evil                  Veteran                                                                                                             Aura of Protection                  Master                                                                                     Blade of Justice                  Master                                                                                                             Celestial Form                  Epic                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                Tier Bonuses                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                             Divine Grace                              Novice                                             Trigger           You attempt a save against a spell, before you roll                                  You call upon your diety’s grace, gaining a +2 circumstance bonus to the save.                                  Glimpse of Redemption                              Novice                                             Trigger           An enemy damages your ally, and both are within 15 feet of you                                  Your foe hesitates under the weight of sin as visions of redemption play in their mind’s eye. The foe must choose one of the following options:     The ally is unharmed by the triggering damage   The triggering damage is reduced by Prof + 2 * your Crusader level. After the damaging effect is applied, the enemy becomes enfeebled 2 until the end of its next turn.                                  Lay on Hands                              Novice                                       Healing                    Positive                    Spell                                                      Cost           1 Mana                    Range           Touch                                  Your hands become infused with positive energy, healing a living creature with a touch. You heal your target 6 HP, and they gain a +2 bonus to AC for 1 round. If you target an undead, they instead take 1d6 radiant damage and must attempt a Fortitude save; if they fail, they also take a -2 penalty to AC for 1 round.   If you spend a second action when using this ability, you also remove one Fear or one effect causing the paralyzed condition on the target, in addition to the other benefits.      Heightened (per +1 Mana)   The amount of healing increases by 6, and the damage to an undead target increases by 1d6                                  Slayer's Oath              Novice                        You’ve sworn to slay a specific type of creature or monster, such as dragons, undead, or evil humanoids. Whenever you hit your sworn foe with a weapon attack, the attack deals an extra Prof damage.   Whenever you encounter your sworn foe, you must attempt to kill it if you have a reasonable chance of success. If you fail to do so, you lose the benefit of this power until you have sufficiently atoned for your actions (as determined by the GM).                                  Litany against Wrath                              Veteran                                       Spell                                                      Cost           3 Mana                    Range           30 feet                    Save           Will                    Duration           1 round                                  You rail against the sin of wrath, punishing the target for attacking good creatures. The target must attempt a Will save. A particularly wrathful creature, such as a Sith Lord or an Angry Marine, has a -10 penalty to its saving throw. The target then becomes temporarily immune to this power for 1 minute.      Heightened (per +1 Mana)   The damage increases by 1d6                                   Critical Success           The target is unaffected                             Success           The first time the target uses a power that deals damage to at least one creature, the target takes 3d6 radiant damage                             Failure           Each time the target uses a power that deals damage to at least one good creature, the target takes 3d6 radiant damage                             Critical Failure           As failure, and the target is enfeebled 2                                               Persistent Smite                              Veteran                                             Trigger           Your Strike hits a creature                                  You surround evil targets in a punishing halo. Your target takes persistent radiant damage equal to your Charisma modifier.                                  Smite Evil                              Veteran                                             Duration           Until the start of your next turn                                  Your weapons become powerful tools against evildoers. Select one foe you can see. Your Strikes against that foe deal an extra 2 + Prof damage.   Whenever the foe attacks one of your allies, the duration extends to the end of that foe’s next turn.                                  Aura of Protection              Master                        You and all allies within 15 feet gain a +2 bonus to saves.                                  Blade of Justice                              Master                        You call upon divine power and make a weapon or unarmed Strike against a foe you have witnessed harming an ally or innocent. The Strike deals two extra weapon damage dice, and you can convert all the physical damage from the attack into radiant damage.                                  Celestial Form              Epic                        You take on a celestial countenance; for example, as an angel with a halo and feathery wings. You gain a fly speed equal to your Speed. You gain darkvision and the celestial trait.",
